wild flooding
Homonym Number:
Word Class:noun
Sense Number:
Definition:a method of surface irrigation (in areas where contour is too difficult for border-dyking or border-ditching, but where ditches are stopped up in high areas to allow flooding over low-lying areas)
Origin:[none]
Register:
Register 2:
Domain:[none]
Region:[none]
